BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 2: First Trimester \(Weeks 1-13\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What's Happening) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (All major organs and body systems are forming. This is the most critical time for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (nutrition quality \(even though you may not feel like eating\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 612.4 Td (Managing Nausea) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 594.4 Td (- Eat small, frequent meals \(every 2-3 hours\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 580.4 Td (- Keep crackers by bedside for morning sickness) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 566.4 Td (- Ginger: Tea, candies, or supplement \(shown to reduce nausea\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.4 Td (- Vitamin B6: 25mg 3x daily \(discuss with provider\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- Cold foods may be tolerated better than hot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- Avoid strong smells and trigger foods) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Stay hydrated \(sip throughout the day\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 480.6 Td (First Trimester Nutrition Priorities) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 462.6 Td (- Folate-rich foods daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 448.6 Td (- Adequate hydration despite nausea) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 434.6 Td (- Whatever you can keep down is okay) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 420.6 Td (- Prenatal vitamin \(try at night if morning sickness\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.6 Td (- Protein when tolerated \(aids nausea\)) Tj ET
